  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager (ACMV)(New Built Project)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for a team of engineers, supervisors and workers to ensure smooth progress during execution of project.</li><li>Main in-charge for the entire phase of the Project Management, from preparation to Site management, and subsequently until completion.</li><li>Good knowledge and experience in engineering design for ACMV, HVAC & Control System</li><li>Well verse in installation of HVAC equipment's chillers, AHU, MV systems, packaged unit, VRV system and split units.</li><li>Ensure on-time submission of shop drawings and equipment/material for approval by consultants and architects.</li><li>Submit variation order cost for additional work to be carried out as per instruction issued by architects and consultants.</li><li>Responsible for the testing and commissioning of the ACMV system.</li><li>Ensure prompt submission of as-built drawings, operation maintenance Manual and conduct training for client during handing over of project upon completion.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Recognized Degree in Mechanical Engineering is preferred, or equivalent.</li><li>Minimum 5 years’ experience in handling Mechanical/Electrical/Fit-out engineering project.</li><li>Strong project management experience, preferably in handling ACMV for industrial or commercial purpose.</li><li>Strong technical knowledge in ACMV</li><li>Possess good people management and interpersonal skills.</li><li>5.5 day work week</li><li>Candidates with more experience might be considered for the Snr PM role</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Ang Hoe Keong | EA Personnel Registration No.: R1106345</strong></p><p><strong>RS Recruitment Agency | EA License No. 17C8809</strong></p>",
